Heat oil in 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Cook chicken in oil 8 to 10 minutes, turning once, until juice is no longer pink when centers of thickest pieces are cut. Remove chicken from skillet; keep warm. Add water to skillet; heat to boiling. Stir in rice and stir-fry sauce; remove from heat. Cover and let stand 5 minutes. While rice is standing, cook vegetables as directed on bag. Serve chicken over rice with vegetables on the side.